<div>	
    <div class="content legal">
        <div class="l-box">
            <h2>How does it work?</h2>
			<p>When your public key is added to a public keyserver open the link: </p>

			<p><span class="marker_success">https://encrypt.to/{your-email}</span></p>

			<p>For example: <a href="/hello@encrypt.to">encrypt.to/hello@encrypt.to</a> belongs to <a href="http://pgpkey.org/pks/lookup?op=get&fingerprint=on&search=0x0CAF1E5B11489A1F"> this public key</a>.</p>

			<p></p>

            <p style="font-size:small;">
                * If not, upload your public key to a <a href="http://pgpkey.org/">public keyserver</a>.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>	
</div>

